ar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Radhakrishnan S. Iyer","active":false,"timeZone":"Asia/Kolkata"},"body":"This is in connection with this post https://engage.eucalyptus.com/customer/en/portal/questions/880139-unable-to-attach-volume-to-windows-instances?new=880139\n\nPlz help me in getting rid-off this issue.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=rk","name":"rk","key":"rk","accountId":"557058:c361950b-7c53-47bd-a5fc-6ae94b148aea","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Radhakrishnan S. Iyer","active":false,"timeZone":"Asia/Kolkata"},"created":"2013-03-14T01:31:54.647-0500","updated":"2013-03-14T01:31:54.647-0500"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/19830/comment/42135","id":"42135","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=rk","name":"rk","key":"rk","accountId":"557058:c361950b-7c53-47bd-a5fc-6ae94b148aea","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Radhakrishnan S. Iyer","active":false,"timeZone":"Asia/Kolkata"},"body":"Ok.. Now, I would like to address this issue.\nAs we have discussed, after volume attachment, the remote desktop connection just dies. This is an after effect of what I feel a problem in eucalyptus itself, not the Microsoft's remote desktop connection. Following are my reasons for the same.\n\n1. When we connect remotely via Microsoft's remote desktop viewer, we entered the \"public IP\" of the virtual instance. After attachment, the connection died and we were helpless. This is because \"public IP\" of instance is \"lost\" after volume attachment.\n\n2. TigerVNC worked well because we were giving the \"IP_address_of_NC\":\"port_of_a_running_virtual_image\" for example,\n10.3.7.150:5900\n10.3.7.150 being our NC and 5900 is the port we got by running netstat command.\nBUT, when we tried \"public IP\" of the virtual machine in the TigerVNC after volume attachment, \"result is still the same!\" No connection. So TigerVNC works for the time being because we are at least able to run the image after volume attachment although in a small window size with no support for scaling in full screen mode. Microsoft's Remote desktop failed because it could not connect to a virtual machine if we give 10.3.7.150:5900 kind of address.\n\n3. Nevertheless, we tried our luck with Chrome's RDP:https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/chrome-rdp/cbkkbcmdlboombapidmoeolnmdacpkch?utm_source=chrome-ntp-icon\nIt turns out that Google also provides a Remote desktop application for connecting to Microsoft images.\nResult the same! We tried connecting without volume attachment, worked like a charm. But when we attached volume, after exactly 7 minutes(yep.. we counted it..) the connection died and we were no longer to connect to that instance. Interestingly, the instance was still accessible via TigerVNC using 10.3.7.150:5900.\n\nSo.. to sum it up, I believe on attaching the volumes, the service in eucalyptus that is responsible for providing public IPs to instances dies and the only way left to access them is via the port number on NC's Ip address(which fortunately is still active :D). because Google is charging $10 on that software of theirs' and I fail to believe that they would let it out without proper testing and moreover same issue replicated in Microsoft's app and also TigerVNC.\n\nSo as I am saying, if it is correct, how to restart that particular service so that we can have those instances get their public IPs? Can you please look into that and let us know?\n\nThanks.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=rk","name":"rk","key":"rk","accountId":"557058:c361950b-7c53-47bd-a5fc-6ae94b148aea","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a492cc38d3ff8072ce8cad3c4db9d1ac?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"http